sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>Controller Manager
    participant Kubelet as kubelet<br/>10250/TCP HTTPS
    participant FeatureServer as Feature Server Pod<br/>Online/Offline/Registry/UI
    participant DB as External Database<br/>(PostgreSQL/Redis/etc.)
    participant ObjStore as S3/GCS<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 1: FeatureStore Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployments, Services,<br/>PVCs, ConfigMaps, RBAC<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Kubelet: Schedule Pod<br/>TLS, Node cert
    Kubelet->>FeatureServer: Start container

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 2: Online Feature Retrieval
    User->>FeatureServer: GET features<br/>80/443 TCP HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: K8s RBAC / OIDC
    FeatureServer->>DB: Query features<br/>Auth: Secret credentials

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 3: Notebook Integration
    User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook with<br/>feast-integration label
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Notebook watch event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read feast-configs-registry<br/>ConfigMap
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create per-Notebook<br/>Feast client ConfigMap

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 4: CronJob Execution
    K8sAPI->>FeatureServer: Start CronJob Pod<br/>(origin-cli)
    FeatureServer->>FeatureServer: feast apply
    FeatureServer->>FeatureServer: feast materialize-incremental
    FeatureServer->>FeatureServer: Call Registry/Online/Offline<br/>80/443 TCP HTTP/HTTPS/gRPC<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
